First off Beaslords getting proc buffs for there pets, Good for them our pets proc automatically with spells stuns and roots, whereas they have to keep buffing there pets and waste a spell slot, we can just summon and forget as long as our pets dont die. <br>
Second, Beastlord pets being able to cross zones.  Remember,SoL is stillin the developmental phase, this may be changed before release, and in all likelyhood if Beastlords can do it they will change our pets to be able to do the same thing. Just because the havent said they will does not mean they wont. <br>
Third, Beastlords pets being the same level as the PC.<br>
This does not mean that their pets will compare to our pets stat wise. Mage pet levels are so importanat to us because our pets are based on the same stats system as PCs of the class the pet represents, I.E. Earth is based on the Warrior, Water = Rouge, etc. So it may be that a Level 34 Mage pet can waste a 44 Beaslord pet while we are getting drunk and laughing at the Beastlords pittiful attempts at hitting out pet. And as for The new Wizard familiar, I have seen some of the preposed stat buffs these bestowe on the Wizard, nice buffs and a neat way to personmalize the wizard class, but not a pet in any sence of the word, I dont even think these new familars can attack at all! So dont worry,  Mages will always hold the title of Masters of Pet Summoning!  <br>
Lastly, Mages not getting root or stun spells. I also used to think that we got shafted by not having these type of spells, but giving us these spells would be a real screw over to Wizards. As it stands now Wizards basic solo tactic is the Root and Nuke. Now if Mages get root spells we could do the same AND still have a powerfull pet backing us. So i dont see Veriant giving us these, however the lack of any help in escaping a bad situation is a big problem so my suggestion is this, how about a earth based quicksand line of spells that slows a target? That way we could cast it on the mob,then retreat to a safe distance and gate.<br>
<br>
But this is all immaterial, I personally love playing my mage, and have no desire to switch to another class no matter what abilities they get, if you are so donw on Mages because you see other classes getting spells you want then go play as one of them. I love my Mage and will keep playing him no matter what other classes get!<br>
<br>
Salodar Magisphere of the SIlver Hawks<br>
Magician of the 40th Circle<br>
Drinal Server<br>
